<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6aa22d6-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s31327"><num value="31327">§ 31327.</num><heading> Forfeiture of mortgagee interest</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The interest of a mortgagee in a documented vessel or a vessel covered by a preferred mortgage under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s31322/d">section 31322(d) of this title</ref> may be terminated by a forfeiture of the vessel for a violation of a law of the United States only if the mortgagee authorized, consented, or conspired to do the act, failure, or omission that is the basis of the violation.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf6aa22d7-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/710/tI/s102/c">Pub. L. 100–710, title I, § 102(c)</ref>, <date date="1988-11-23">Nov. 23, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/4746">102 Stat. 4746</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
